efficiently material can be transported from the inner few parsecs to
the accretion disc. Our results are incompatible with the simplest form
of mass quenching where massive galaxies host higher accretion rate
AGNs. Furthermore, if reaching a certain Eddington ratio is a sufficient
condition for maintenance mode, it can occur in all red galaxies, not
just the most massive ones.},
